HEADWORD: Disgospel
<hw>Dis*gos"pel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be
inconsistent with, or act contrary to, the precepts of the gospel; to
pervert the gospel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

